<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,222,499]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">
A Western Palearctic genus with two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sternlicht" authorityName="Sternlicht" box="[670,892,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Chilaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="israeli">
<emphasis box="[670,775,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">C. israeli</emphasis>
Sternlicht
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Giraud)" authorityName="Giraud" baseAuthorityName="Giraud" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[947,1153,222,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Chilaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[947,1045,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">C. nitida</emphasis>
(Giraud)
</taxonomicName>
, inducing catkin and leaf galls on oaks from section 
<emphasis box="[460,538,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Cerris.</emphasis>
The asexual and sexual generations are known for both species, developing in detachable leaf galls and catkin galls, respectively. Morphologically, the genus closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1388,295,318]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1248,1388,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Dryocosmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1881" box="[151,309,331,355]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Plagiotrochus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Plagiotrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Ros-Farre, P. &amp; Melika, G." box="[323,619,330,355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="167 - 178" refId="ref35694" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Ros-Farre, P. &amp; Melika, G. (2003 b) Revision of the genus Chilaspis Mayr, 1881 (Hymenoptera: Cynipoidea: Cynipidae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, New Series, 39 (2), 167 - 178." type="journal article" year="2003">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[482,530,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. 2003b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Ide, T. &amp; Yang, M. M. &amp; Penzes, Z. &amp; Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[631,841,330,355]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref34873" refString="Melika, G., Pujade-Villar, J., Abe, Y., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Wachi, N., Ide, T., Yang, M. M., Penzes, Z., Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2010) Palaearctic oak gallwasps galling oaks (Quercus) in the section Cerris: re-appraisal of generic limits, with descriptions of new genera and species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 2470, 1 - 79." type="journal article" year="2010">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[717,766,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), but its synonymization with 
<taxonomicName box="[1182,1322,331,354]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1322,331,354]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Dryocosmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Acs, Z. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Penzes, Z. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="70 - 80" refId="ref32601" refString="Acs, Z., Melika, G., Penzes, Z., Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Stone. G. N. (2007) The phylogenetic relationships between Dryocosmus, Chilaspis and allied genera of oak gallwasps (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae: Cynipini). Systematic Entomology, 32, 70 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2006.00351. x" type="journal article" year="2007">
√Åcs 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
was premature and did not incorporate adequately molecular or morphological characters found in other cynipid genera (e.g., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1881" box="[393,511,403,427]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Aphelonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,511,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Aphelonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[576,701,403,426]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,701,403,426]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Neuroterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In a more recent phylogenetic reconstruction, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giraud" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1252,1353,403,427]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Chilaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis box="[1252,1353,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">C. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Chilaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="israeli">
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,403,426]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,223,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">israeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a strongly-supported monophyletic clade together with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1881" box="[957,1115,438,462]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Plagiotrochus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1115,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Plagiotrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and were clearly separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stone et al. 2009)" authorityName="Stone" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Stone" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[212,571,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Dryocosmus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[212,352,475,498]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">Dryocosmus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stone, G. N. &amp; Hernandez-Lopez, A. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Pierro, E. di &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Cook, J. M." box="[366,563,475,499]" pageId="22" pageNumber="473" pagination="854 - 869" refId="ref36479" refString="Stone, G. N., Hernandez-Lopez, A., Nicholls, J. A., Pierro, E. di., Pujade-Villar, J., Melika, G. &amp; Cook, J. M. (2009) Extreme host plant conservatism during at least 20 million years of host plant pursuit by oak gallwasps. Evolution, 63, 854 - 869. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1558 - 5646.2008.00604. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Stone 
<emphasis box="[439,488,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="473">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
